description: As a square array T(n,k) by antidiagonals, number of ways of partitioning k into up to n parts each no more than 5, or into up to 5 parts each no more than n; as a triangle t(n,k), number of ways of partitioning n into exactly k parts each no more than 6 (i.e., of arranging k indistinguishable standard dice to produce a total of n).
